  "They are coming.
   Atom by atom... they will coil around us...
   and take all that we are.
   There is one way to confront this threat.
   By reuniting the 24 warring Houses of our own empire.
   We have forgotten the Unforgettable...
   the last to unify our tribes - Kahless -
   together, under one creed... remain Klingon!
   That is why we light our beacon this day. To assemble our people.
   To lock arms against those whose fatal greeting is..."

The speech concludes with the words (in Federation Standard): "We come in peace."

These lines about Kahless were repeated in several episodes of {Star Trek Discovery:src} (with minor variations, see below).

▶ {'Iv wInej?:sen@@'Iv:ques:1h, wI-:v, nej:v}
  "Whom do we seek?"

▶ {qeylIS.:sen@@qeylIS:n}
  "Kahless."

▶ {chay' wISam?:sen@@chay':ques, wI-:v, Sam:v}
  "How do we find him?"

▶ {matay'taHvIS.:sen@@ma-:v, tay':v, -taH:v, -vIS:v}
  "Together."

▶ {qeylIS, maleghmeH yIwovmoH.:sen@@qeylIS:n:name, ma-:v, legh:v, -meH:v, yI-:v, wov:v, -moH:v}
  "Kahless, give us light to see."

▶ {reH.:sen@@reH:adv}
  "Forever."

▶ {wInejtaHvIS reH So''egh'a'?:sen@@wI-:v, nej:v, -taH:v, -vIS:v, reH:adv, So':v:1, -'egh:v, -'a':v}
  "Will he hide from us always?"

▶ {not.:sen@@not:adv}
  "Never."

These sentences were used by {lIr'el:n:name} to activate {voq:n:name}.[2]

The last words of {tIquvma:n:name} before he died were a version of these lines, which he referred to as "the words we said as children in Kahless' honor". This version has the line {jIjaHmeH yIwovmoH:sen@@jI-:v, jaH:v, -meH:v, yI-:v, wov:v, -moH:v}, instead of {qeylIS, maleghmeH yIwovmoH.:sen:nolink}.[1] When Ash Tyler was sentenced to death, he alluded to these lines by saying {qeylIS, jIleghmeH yIwovmoH. reH.:sen@@qeylIS:n:name, jI-:v, legh:v, -meH:v, yI-:v, wov:v, -moH:v, reH:adv} "Give me light to see, forever."[3] It seems that this sentence can be adapted by the speaker for the specific occasion.

